        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The primary difference lies in the 12V power connector: ATX 3.0 uses the 12VHPWR connector (which had melting issues if not fully seated), while ATX 3.1 adopts the safer 12V-2x6 connector with shorter sense pins."
